text.__SUMMARY__: Acacia argyraea is a shrub belonging to the genus Acacia and the subgenus Juliflorae. It is native to an area of the Kimberley region of Western Australia, to the Northern Territory and Queensland.The silvery-grey shrub typically grows to a height of 0.8 to 3 metres (3 to 10 ft). It blooms from April to July producing yellow flowers.
